reviews.headline: It was okay
reviews.comments: It was an okay mascara. I applied very little and it still smudged and left me with raccoon eyes. If you don't have a problem with smudging then this will work great for you!

reviews.headline: Waterproof?
reviews.comments: Only lasts a couple of hours before it starts to smear

reviews.headline: Great lift
reviews.comments: First time I purchased this mascara.  I always have to buy waterproof.  It has great lift, which is always a challenge for my eyelashes.  The only thing that I don't care for is it's not totally smudge proof.  Lower lash smudging & a bit on the upper lid towards the end of the day.

reviews.headline: I love it!!!
reviews.comments: My eyelashes the past few years have been struggling to maintain a curl with mascara on and I tried everything, but this right here takes the cake! Not only does this give me length, volume, and holds a curl, but it also withstands sweat from this Texas weather!

reviews.headline: Absolutely love this mascara
reviews.comments: If you want lashes for days that don't clump together, this is for you

reviews.headline: Nice with challenges
reviews.comments: It's still a good product

reviews.headline: BadGal Volumizing Waterproof Mascara
reviews.comments: I really miss the original BadGal Waterproof Mascara. I've tried All of Benefits waterproof mascaras. I am not happy with any of them. I've tried numerous waterproof mascaras in various price ranges but none have made as happy as I was with the original BadGal Waterproof Mascara. My search will continue. Surely, I am not the only one who misses the original? I wish the original BadGal Waterproof Mascara would make comeback.

reviews.headline: Quality of product is BAD and not in a good way.
reviews.comments: I had been purchasing for years and in the past year, the quality has declined. It is clumpy in it's container and on lashes. I notified the maker and they said product hasn't changed without any hope in improving.

reviews.headline: Not the best one
reviews.comments: Keeps your eye lashes up, but its super hard to put it, it crumbs and the worst part it is that it takes forever to take off and you can loose some eyelashes, that's a bummer.

reviews.headline: Smudges
reviews.comments: This mascara makes my lashes look great. But it smudges/runs. Which is a bummer because it doesn't last during my 12 hour shifts. I end up with racoon eyes.

reviews.headline: Not as good as I thought
reviews.comments:
I bought this for a trip to the beach needing a waterproof mascara.  So I used it for that week.  Great at making your lashes look longer and thicker.  Also it never came off in the water.
  The problem was the at it felt.  It made my lashes feel heaving even with only a little.  So I was pulling at my lashes and and picking off the mascara because it was so annoying.  So no, I won't buy it again.

reviews.headline: Decent, but not as good as the original
reviews.comments: I love the original/non-waterproof Bad Gal Bang because it creates wonderful length and volume, but always seems to smudge onto my undereye area. So nauturally I wanted to try the waterproof version. The waterproof formula does not create the same length and volume as the original. I had to apply multiple coats and still not obtain the volume it promised and that I desired. The formula seems thin and dry-ish. On the bright side, I was able to remove it easily using micellar water. For the price, it doesn't deliver. There are much better drugstore options.

reviews.headline: Best Mascara ever
reviews.comments: I love this mascara! I first when I bought it I used to hate because it was so hard to take off at night. However, with a good waterproof makeup remover this would be the best. It gives me length and stays on as long as I want. I also have very short straight lashes so this gives me the opposite look when I wear it.

reviews.headline: This is the best
reviews.comments: This is now my new go to mascara

reviews.headline: Not a fan
reviews.comments: This mascara was recommended to me by a sales associate, and I was very disappointed. It made my eyelashes stick together, and it's really hard to wash off. Will not be buying again.

reviews.headline: Twice the price for basic performance
reviews.comments: I wanted something better than my drugstore go-to (Maybelline). This did not perform any better but was twice the price. The waterproof version also was smearing by the end of the day.
It holds a curl perfectly and gives me a good amount of length, it can be a little clumpy but it is a great mascara!!

reviews.headline: Only buy if you like raccoon eyes!
reviews.comments: I was looking for a mascara that would not transfer so much, I typically bought a Tarte brand. I decided to try Badgal Bang waterproof. It transferred from the start, I had raccoon eyes by mid morning. Every time I went to the restroom I had to try and wipe it off from under my eyes. I returned and exchanged for an Hourglass brand.

reviews.headline: I love the lush look it gives my lashes!
reviews.comments: The lush look it gives my lashes makes them look more like I really have lashes instead the sparse lashes I have.  The mascara doesn't come off easily so, if I'm careful with my nighttime routine, I look like I have mascara on the next morning ‚Äî and no smudges on my pillowcase!

reviews.headline: Not for me
reviews.comments: This is a nice m√°scara. It is a very deep black, which I like. However, the formula is very wet. So when trying to apply another coat it ends up clumpy. I would not buy again.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I received BADgal BANG! Waterproof Volumizing Mascara gifted by benefitcosmatics , The key features of the BADgal BANG! Waterproof Volumizing Mascara are:

1. Lightweight yet intensely bold: This mascara provides a bold and dramatic look to your lashes without weighing them down.

2. Ultra-light aero particles: The mascara contains ultra-light aero particles that lift your lashes, giving them a fuller and longer appearance.

3. Waterproof formula: The mascara is waterproof, making it resistant to water and ensuring that it stays put even in challenging conditions.

4. Smudge-proof: You don't have to worry about smudging or smearing throughout the day, as this mascara is smudge-proof.

5. Volumizing effect: The mascara adds noticeable volume to your lashes, making them look more full and voluminous.

6. Lengthening effect: It also provides a lengthening effect, making your lashes appear longer and more defined.

7. Long-wearing: The mascara lasts a full 36 hours without losing its intensity or flaking off, allowing you to wear it all day and night without any touch-ups.

8. Buildable: The mascara is buildable, meaning you can easily layer it for a more dramatic look or apply a single coat for a more natural appearance.

These key features make the BADgal BANG! Waterproof Volumizing Mascara a standout product that delivers on its promises of bold, volumized, and long-lasting lashes.
faceoff_positive.headline: Amazing!

faceoff_negative.comments:
This mascara wins my own personal award for the worst mascara I've bought since I still bought drugstore makeup as a teenager. Its bringing back all the worst memories!! So fun.

TLDR; impossible to remove completely, wake up with racoon eyes no matter how much makeup remover/face wash/showering/paint thinner you use the night before, smears if you make any facial expression, I wouldnt reccoment to my worst enemy.

I got this because the ulta store I went to was out of Lancome D√©finicils which is my go-to because I prefer the "no makeup" makeup look and D√©finicils can achieve that easily. One of the sales associates recommended it to me when I told her I was looking for D√©finicils. This is a sorry replacement for that mascara. I always want waterproof, becuase I spend a lot of time outdoors and sometimes its hard to know what I will get into during the day and I work out in mascara. Maybe thats the problem and why this mascara was so bad‚Äîbut either way it is horrible. Within hours ill have a slight shadow under my eyes from the smearing and I noticed occasional flaking as well. The worst part is, not only does it smear while you wear it, but somehow, its also IMPOSSIBLE to remove it all when youre done for the day. I never thought that would be a problem, but its really bad! How can it be both?? No matter what I do and what I use, I wake up in the morning with it smeared under my eyes. I use multiple different options for makeup remover-micclear water, Clinique take the day off balm, oil, and a makeup wipe AND I wash my face every night, sometimes twice. Nothing I do gets this mascara off in one night. That might sound good, but when the mascara still flakes and smears and looks bad all day its not worth it!!
faceoff_negative.headline: Wow! Haven't purchased a mascara this bad in a while!
